Question
========

In a study involving 30 subjects, the variable *Blood Pressure* is predicted from *Weight* and *Age*. The square sum of the regression is 427, the square sum of the residuals is 4580, and the total square sum is 5007.

The multiple correlation (R) of this regression model is

  
Answerlist
----------
* 0.085
* 0.093
* 0.292
* 0.305

Solution
========

Answerlist
----------
* Incorrect
* Incorrect
* Correct
* Incorrect
